  "body": "### Description\r\nAfter following [this document](https://hackmd.io/@StefanBratanov/BkMlo1RO9), if the Beacon node is not in sync, then:\r\n\r\nThe Beacon node raises this error (Error 503):\r\n```\r\n2022-06-10 10:52:27.103 ERROR - Failed to process request to URL http://kiln-teku-beacon-0-rpc.ethereum-common:5051/eth/v1/validator/duties/sync/20479\r\njava.lang.IllegalStateException: Content required for status code 503 but not provided\r\nat com.google.common.base.Preconditions.checkState(Preconditions.java:562) ~[guava-31.1-jre.jar:?]\r\nat tech.pegasys.teku.infrastructure.restapi.endpoints.JavalinRestApiRequest.respondWithCode(JavalinRestApiRequest.java:133) ~[teku-infrastructure-restapi-develop.jar:22.5.2+95-gab816b2]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe Validator raises this error (Error 500):\r\n```\r\n2022-06-10 10:52:27.106 ERROR - Failed to request validator duties for epoch 20479. Retrying after delay.\r\njava.util.concurrent.CompletionException: java.lang.RuntimeException: Unexpected response from Beacon Node API (url = http://kiln-teku-beacon-0-rpc.ethereum-common:5051/eth/v1/validator/duties/sync/20479, status = 500)\r\nat java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture.encodeThrowable(Unknown Source) ~[?:?]\r\nat java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture.completeThrowable(Unknown Source) ~[?:?]\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote no more error appears when the Beacon node is in sync.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nFollow [this document](https://hackmd.io/@StefanBratanov/BkMlo1RO9)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nNo discrepency between errors, and for UX design, maybe replace StackTrace by an Error or Warning log.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nSee Description\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [How regularly does it occur?]\r\nAlways when beacon node is not in sync.\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: `teku/v22.5.2+89-g1687447/linux-aarch_64/-eclipseadoptium-openjdk64bitservervm-java-17` (develop)",
